One of the five hardcore criminals who escaped from Thika law courts on Tuesday was arrested yesterday. Thika police chief Erastus Muthamia said police will soon catch the other four.Speaking on the phone, Muthamia said the five were among criminals from Industrial Area GK Prison in Nairobi. They were taken toThika law courts for the mention of their pending cases.The five are facing various charges of violent robberies. They used master keys to open the cell doors and escaped. Muthamia said investigations have been launched. He said it is still early to establish whether there were officers or court orderlies involved.It is not clear how the inmates got the keys since they are thoroughly checked when going on and leaving the prison.It appears they got the master keys while in transist from Industrial Area or at the Thika law courts.